                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d284">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Goschen</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-08-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 25, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In response to the inquiry the British ambassador
                    made of me yesterday, when handing me a memorandum of Lord Kimberley’s views
                    touching the effect of the recent tariff legislation upon the commercial
                    agreements made with the West Indies under section 3 of the McKinley act, I have
                    the honor to say that the sections to which his lordship refers would, upon the
                    new tariff act becoming a law, operate to cancel those agreements.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q. Gresham.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
